      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Connections of BLUE LIGHT DISCO (1) could not have hoped to find a more suitable race than what he is presented with here. Freshened after the adequate debut in a handy Pakenham maiden, he improved again at start No 2 at the same track and then just found the nippy Catwalk Icon too slippery last start. The three starts to date have been in races of more depth than this and the only negative here is the outside gate, but the small field helps in that regard. ROUGH ENUFF (5) disappointed at Pakenham last start but was well-backed off a good run in town the start prior and might be worth another chance. WRITTEN STORY (7) was a big improver second-up when put on speed and she can give a sight from the good draw. Bit of a gap to LOVE ME TOMORROW (7), who needs to bounce back after a poor run last start but was good on debut, then an even bigger gap to the rest.",
